task.summary: File for efficient frontier finance analysis, linear regression, and fund analysis, as well as utils
Plot for prices and volatility on two axes per plot
Updated EfficientFrontier, New_Fund_Analysis, and utils to all run with working examples. Source data can be found in data repository
New Fund Analysis including Bollinger Band plots for dataset
Added drop flag to get rid of NaN rows
Added Random Walks and Stationarity (for time series)
Updated to include static methods transform
Added finance-database, Intro to Random Walks, decorators, New Fund Analysis, updated Utils, FIFA player analysis
Updated EfficientFrontier, New_Fund_Analysis, and utils to all run with working examples. Source data can be found in data repository

Updated the following: - utils: optimised datePlusTenorNew for lookbacks, added array_to_clipboard function. Needs pyperclip - New_Fund_Analysis: added wkdir specification, startDate and endDate will autopopulate if not specified. NaNs no longer dropped, included in analysis & summary tables. Summary table will include whole lookback for all securities. - README: added prerequisite of pyperclip
Updated README to reflect work done, updated summary table logic for printing output
New module to give holding period return of security data- inputs are dates transacted and units. Summary and detailed table given as outputs
